quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  11,38,"So he started constructing the Ark, and every time some chiefs of his people passed by him, they ridiculed him. He said, “If you ridicule us now, we will soon ridicule you as you are ridiculing us.",""
  11,39,"You will come to know who will be afflicted with a disgracing punishment<sup>18</sup>, and upon whom will descend an everlasting punishment<sup>19</sup>.”","[18] In this life.\n [19] In the Hereafter."
  11,40,"When Our command came and the oven overflowed, We said, “Take on board a pair from every species and your family<sup>20</sup> – except those who have already been decreed [to drown]<sup>21</sup> – and those who believe.” But none believed with him except a few.","[20] i.e., Noah’s family. [21] Such as his son."
  11,41,"Noah said, “Board it; in the name of Allah it sails and anchors. My Lord is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.”",""
  11,42,"As it sailed with them through waves like mountains, Noah called out to his son<sup>22</sup>, who had kept himself apart, “O my son, come aboard with us, and do not be with the disbelievers.”","[22] Who was a disbeliever."
  11,43,"He said, “I will take shelter on a mountain which will save me from the water.” Noah said, “Today no one will be saved from Allah’s punishment except those on whom He may have mercy.” Thereupon the waves came between them, and he was among those who were drowned.",""
  11,44,"And it was said, “O earth, swallow up your water. O sky, withhold [your rain]!” The water subsided and the command was fulfilled, and the Ark settled on Mount Judi, and it was said, “Away with the wrongdoing people!”",""
  11,45,"Noah called out to his Lord, saying, “My Lord, my son is one of my family<sup>23</sup>, and Your promise is true and You are the Most Just of all judges!”","[23] To save his family members from drowning."
